repo.name: cython

body:
Treating the following as obscure:
    * Windows Arm64
    * Windows 32bit x86
    * Linux 32bit x86
    * Mac OS x86_64
    
and building them with Python 3.9

PR includes #7226

I wonder if it'll need to include https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7187 - we'll find out I suspect.

comment_data.body: Despite what [the documentation says](https://cibuildwheel.pypa.io/en/stable/changelog/#v250), this doesn't appear to be true in practice - it's building multiple versions of the same thing.
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -3,9 +3,23 @@ requires = ["setuptools"]
 
 [tool.cibuildwheel]
 build-verbosity = 2
-skip = ["pp*", "gp*", "cp31?t-*", "cp36*", "cp37*"]
+skip = [
+    "pp*", "gp*", "cp31?t-*", "cp36*", "cp37*",
+    # The platforms below are non-core platforms that we're providing
+    # Stable ABI (>3.9) wheels to. Python 3.8 is excluded and will use
+    # pure-Python wheels. cibuildwheel will identify Stable ABI wheels and
+    # only build them for the one Python version. It will test them for all
+    # Python versions though.

comment_data.body:
It may be the `only` option that's stopping it from working. 

I also don't know why I seem to have broken the 3.13t tests (which should be unaffected)

comment_data.body:
If you ask for `AMD64` specifically, then you don't need to accommodate Windows-ARM.
```suggestion
              && cibuildwheel --print-build-identifiers --platform windows --archs AMD64 \
              | jq -nRc '{"only": inputs, "os": "windows-2022"}' \
```
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -67,16 +67,19 @@ jobs:
         # Nb. keep cibuildwheel version pin consistent with job below
         run: pipx install cibuildwheel==3.2.0
       - id: set-matrix
+        # sed substitutions for ARM in the matrix below are unused (because ARM is done in the Stable ABI)
+        # but are left for convenience if we ever want to change that.
         run: |
           MATRIX=$(
             {
-              cibuildwheel --print-build-identifiers --platform linux \
+              cibuildwheel --print-build-identifiers --platform linux --archs x86_64 \
               | jq -nRc '{"only": inputs, "os": "ubuntu-latest"}' \
               | sed -e '/aarch64/s|ubuntu-latest|ubuntu-24.04-arm|' \
               && cibuildwheel --print-build-identifiers --platform macos \
               | jq -nRc '{"only": inputs, "os": "macos-latest"}' \
-              && cibuildwheel --print-build-identifiers --platform windows \
-              | jq -nRc '{"only": inputs, "os": "windows-2022"}'
+              && cibuildwheel --print-build-identifiers --platform windows --archs AMD64 \
+              | jq -nRc '{"only": inputs, "os": "windows-2022"}' \
+              | sed -e '/arm64/s|windows-2022|windows-11-arm|'

comment_data.body:
I left this in mainly so it was easy to change in future. But very happy to remove it if you want - it is pointless right now.

(I think your suggestion needs the last trailing slash removed though, to put it back to how it was)

Maybe we can comment it out to keep it as a reminder that we could use ARM based runners also on Windows?

> your suggestion needs the last trailing slash removed

I considered that but kept the trailing slash for the same reason I like trailing commas, to avoid touching the unrelated last line when we add more cases after it.

commit.message:
Improve Limited API handling in setup.py

The main aim is to bump the default version to 3.9. But I've
also made it a little more configurable so that it's possible
to pick the version.

Serve "obscure" platforms with Limited API wheels

Treating the following as obscure:
* Windows Arm64
* Linux Arm64
* Windows 32bit x86
* Linux 32bit x86

and building them with Python 3.9
